# Python conventions

- Use `from __future__ import annotations` in every module
- Type hints on all function signatures
- JSON fields from Polymarket APIs may arrive as strings or native types — always handle both (see `_parse_json_field` in ingestion)
- Polymarket has no `resolution` field — resolution is derived from `outcomePrices` (winner gets price "1")
- LLM responses may be wrapped in markdown fences or contain preamble text — always strip fences and extract JSON with `{`/`}` finding before parsing
- Scoring signals return floats in [0, 1] range
- Use Rich for all CLI output (progress bars, tables, panels) — no bare `print()`
- DB access via `get_conn()` context manager from `trawler.db`
- Commit after each record during long-running operations (scoring) for interrupt safety
